        "id": 1002230
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-04-22T15:12:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "From my POV (and my teammates), it\u0027s not critical CVE indeed. Realistically, an attacker should have access to a trusted authority in order to be able to issue trusted certificate. A company might have multiple brands/domains (like macys.com and bloomingdales.com), should they use separated infra, while using the same certificate authority, an attacker may issue root@com certificate to access both of the realms.",
      "parentUuid": "dc856517_95dc12ec",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 10,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 10,
        "endChar": 70
      },
      "revId": "9b65f696ec3ecd86db80848ea41d5b00ff44bade",
